beer_description: Bernsteinfarben in der Optik, ?berzeugt Allg?uer B?ble Bier mit karamellmalzigen Eindr?cken und zugleich leicht herber Note. Ein herzhaftes, s?ffiges Traditionsbier, das schon unsere Gro?v?ter liebten. Perfekt zu w?rzigen Braten, kr?ftigen K?sesorten oder deftigen Eint?pfen.

Nat?rlich w?rzig, mit viel Vitamin B aus der Bierhefe und feinherb gehopft, ist das nat?rliche Zwickelbier etwas Besonderes und ganzj?hrig in der B?gelflasche erh?ltlich. Der ideale Genuss zu Gefl?gel und Salat.

Bernsteinfarbe in der Optik, ausgewogen mild, harmonisch und rund, mit intensivem Dunkelmalzaroma. Der ideal Genuss zu leichten Salaten, mildem K?se und feinem Fisch. Now specifically labelled as their Dunkel Weizen.

Rund, weich, frisch und spritzig zugleich, ist ein echter Genuss nach guter alter Tradition. Allg?uer Brauhaus Orginal empfiehlt sich zu kalten Platten und Canap?s, deftigen Braten und Eint?pfen, mild-w?rzigen Weichk?se und halbfestem Schnittk?se.

Kernig im Antrunk, vereinen sich markant nussige Akzente mit einer harmonisch eingebundenen Hopfenw?rze am Gaumen zu einem geschmeidig Runden und vollen Genuss. Ausgezeichnete Kombinationen ergeben sich mit mild-w?rzigem Streich- und Ziegenfrischk?se, kalten Braten und Brotzeittellern, aber auch zu w?rzigen Cremesuppen und Eintopfgerichten.
Unfiltered, golden, sweet and malty

Draft 5.1% ABV - Bottle 5.6% ABV.

Ringwood's most iconic beer was first brewed in late 1979 without a name. A competition in the local press inspired Joe Leedham from Broadstone, Dorset to come up with a suitable suggestion!

Nose:
Peppery, spicy aroma with a hint of apples.
Palate:
Luscious balance of grain and hop in the mouth. Bitter sweet finish with delicate fruit notes.

Comments:
Warm, rounded yet surprisingly delicate pale strong beer.

This dark IPA is fully black in color, with nutty, roasty malt character, moderate body, with full, bright hop bitterness and aroma. De-husked black malt provides color and roastiness without astringent sharpness and dark caramel and special roast also deepen the color while imparting mild sweetness with lots of toasty complexity and depth. Newport, Palisade, Glacier and Ahtanum hops create multiple layers of crisp American hop character with no harsh edges.

Cantillon Monk's Caf? Cuv?e Kriek is a kriek blend made specifically for Monk's Caf? in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania. The fruit was a Morello (variety: Kelleris) sour cherry sourced in Belgium. The cask was hand selected by Tom Peters of Monk's Caf? and Jean Van Roy.
beer_name: Monk's Caf? Cuvee de Monk's Kriek

A traditional Czech pale beer of a lower volume characterized by its fresh taste, light golden colour, pleasant yeast aroma as well as mild bitterness.

The Original Hemp Ale: Humboldt Brown Ale is brewed with toasted hemp seeds that add a unique, herb-accented flavor. But we didn?t stop there- the American hops create a perfect balance to the darker malts in this brew.

An arabier is a pure malt beer 8?vol/alc brewed with flower Nugget-hops from Poperinge. It has the special dry-hopping taste and aroma, so appreciated by beer lovers all over the world. It is one of the two main beers from De Dolle Brouwers throughout the year. Aging time is limited due to the fact that hop bitterness is declining with the time. Store arabier cool and dark and serve cool at 10?C. Cheers!
A Colorado collaboration. Rich, malty Eisbock, with caramel, roast, raisin and prune notes.

The newest addition to our year round line, Legend Hopfest begins with a sturdy barley malt background including Munich and aromatic malts, as well as a few medium kilned malts producing a rich , deep orange colored beer.  Step two, the hops; Hopfest sports a distinct pine/fruit aroma. Expect an intensely flavored brew, with hop flavor lasting throughout. There is a toasty, earthy background, adding a rich, malty dimension to the long finish. The end result is a full flavored IPA with a strong malt backbone and long satisfying hop finish.   ABV 6.5%
Our Pale is an aggressively hopped, with immense overtones of grapefruit and tangerine wrapped in a delicately refined body of pale barley and wheat.
Rich malt flavor with a roast and toasted finish. This baby's got back!
Apricot Wheat Ale blends various barley malts with malted wheat and natural apricot essence to create an original-tasting beer with a clean, fruit nose
Session India Pale Lager. Green Thumb is a refreshing hoppy lager, light in body but BIG on hop flavor. Brewed with Columbus and Cascade hops and dry-hopped with Chinook hops.

We love the piney, fruity flavors of Simcoe? hops. This is a classic pale ale, single-hopped and dry-hopped with Simcoe. We cold condition this beer and give it a restrained malt profile, so the hops really pop, like flora in spring. Our friends Patrick, Jason and Brad grow these luscious hops and we hope you enjoy them as much as we do.
Aged 6 months in Jack Daniels barrels.

The Hangman is a big, brash American-style Pale Ale that features a huge hit of citrus and stone fruit hop notes on the nose. Brewed with American Ale yeast and a solid malt backbone ? Crystal and Carapils to be exact ? The Hangman showcases Cascade and Liberty hops, with plenty thrown late in the kettle for extra flavour.

Dark Amber by design. The over 100 pounds of sweet and tart cherries added during fermentation add a distinctive light pink hue to the beer and head. Beyond color the cherries offer a cherry forward flavor that does not dominate.

This is a traditionally crafted India Pale Ale with a malt-led ?avour and character. On the nose, our IPA provides a delightful malt aroma. On the palate it delivers clean and refreshing light malt notes combined with the classic strong hop ?avour, and ?nishes with a crisp bitterness.
We use Pale Ale and Crystal malts in our IPA alongside Fuggles and Goldings hops.
Made with ginger and lemonade to impart an interesting citrus aroma & ginger bite. Silver Medal Winner Specialty Beer at 2001, 2002, & 2003 Great American Beer Festival.

Our winter offering is here to quell your shivers and get you through the coldest of nights. A rich marriage of hops and barley to cast light upon the evening and melt your mind out of the snowdrifts. Old Man Winter?s earthy hue and thickness lace around the glass, inviting you to linger in its warmth and share the spirits of the season with your friends and family. A deceptively strong brew, it?s best to sit and ponder with this old man, sip by sip.

beer_description:
Probably the best beer in the world, and the flagship brand in Carlsberg Group's portfolio. A regular in millions of bars across 140 countries worldwide, it is a truly international beer brand.

Hordeum vulgare. That?s the Latin name for barley, but there?s nothing vulgar about it. In fact, it is a rather special malting barley we use. We have our own Barley Breeding Group, which works in close contact with our brewmasters.

The group selects the barley with the best traits and grows it in our research fields, using only traditional breeding methods, 100% free of genetic modifications. Considering that Carlsberg is made from 100% pure malt i.e. no adjuncts it could take some years before we breed the necessary amount of barley. Probably worth the effort.

Hops are our secret ingredient. Of course it is no secret that we use hops in our beer, but the types we use are prepared according to a secret recipe that?s exclusive to us. It?s called the Carlsberg Aroma Hop Extract and nobody but us at Carlsberg can use it. After all, there can only be one best beer in the world.

Yeast is at the heart of our history. In 1879, Carlsberg was the first brewery to produce a purified brewer?s yeast, the Saccharomyces Carlsbergensis. Since then we?ve been constantly working to improve our yeast?s taste and the stability of our beer. We do it by using a classic breeding method, which means it can take up to 20 trials and several years to obtain a new yeast strain that?s good enough for brewing

beer_description:
?kologisk India Pale Ale er brygget med inspiration fra den amerikanske IPA-tradition, hvilket giver en st?rkere ?l end den engelske IPA og med mere humle. Den store m?ngde humle tilf?jer god skarp bitterhed i den fyldige smag, og en frisk duft af citrus, frugt og blomster. Farven er korngul og vi har brygget med de fineste ?kologiske malte. Humlen er den prim?re smagsgiver i ?llen, og balanceres med fylde fra malten og alkohol fra g?ren.

Anvendelse:
?kologisk IPA er l?kker p? en sommerdag - indbydende, k?lende og l?skende. Den passer fremragende til snacks og krydret mad, hvor dens bitterhed giver det helt rigtige modspil.

Single hopped Australian pale ale. A new beer fom the team here at Thornbridge ?Galaxia?. The name might suggest it?s from the stars but it refers to this being a single hopped pale ale ? a beer brewed to showcase the Australian hop variety Galaxy.

Caolan Vaughan our resident antipodean says ?Using our fantastic pale ale recipe allows this stunning hop to transform this beer into a pleasurable experience in a glass - one for all hop lovers?. The Galaxy hop imparts striking beautiful aromas of mango, guava and grapefruit. While providing an intensely tingling bitter finish. ABV varies between 4.5% and 5.2%

beer_description: This is our 4.6% straw coloured premium refreshing ale. It goes well with spicy foods and is available at our Brewery Tap, in cask and in bottles.
Full-bodied imperial stout brewed with 44 pounds of chocolate and aged with fresh cocoa nibs and whole vanilla beans.
A smooth, creamy oatmeal stout with a light sweetness and dry finish. Full roasted flavor without a touch of harshness, often poured on nitro-tap.
Our Cowabunga Porter aged in bourbon barrels with vanilla beans for several months.

A refreshing, unfiltered wheat beer that showcases the unique, but subtle, fruit and spice character from the classical southern German yeast strain we use. In the spirit of the German purity law, this beer is brewed using only malt, hops, yeast and water. Please enjoy this beer WITHOUT a fruit garnish, as it is brewed specifically to rely its own beautiful balance of flavors.
Our English Sweet Stout brewed with 22 pounds of Belgian bittersweet chocolate and aged with 10 pounds of cocoa nibs and Madagascar vanilla beans for a cold weather treat.
Homebrew!

Absolutely smashing IPA with loads of American hops and made with a typical American ale yeast. You will maybe be amazed at the equal balance between hop and malt, wrestling to see who wins.  Absent from this double is that very grassy, in-your-face hoppiness that makes some doubles difficult to quaff. Truly a comfortable and remarkable face adjuster.
English Red Ale
Hop Session is in. Starting with a blend of west coast hops for a balanced, bitter effect. We close the session out by late hopping the beer for a nice resiny mouth feel.

Our Dry Hopped American Pale Ale (APA) is charged with American hops to create a bold, aromatic ale. Assertive hop flavor joins the pine/citrus aroma characteristic of American hops to balance the full body provided by North American malts. After fermentation, the beer circulates through a bed of whole-cone Cascade and Chinook hops, boosting the distinctive hop aroma of this satisfying ale.
A much stronger version of our original Ten Penny recipe.  This beer is a dark brown ale, topped by a thick, loose tan head
Brewed and dry-hopped with Amarillo and Simcoe hops, this bitter, flavorful and uber-aromatic brew is ready for those Hard Times.
Honoring the 2004 Red Sox.  Ruby-colored ale modeled after the pre-prohibition red beers of 1918.

beer_description: Inspired by Trappist brewing tradition, this brew offers honeyed sweetness on the tongue and a dry finish.
A sliced winter warmer with the flavor of Christmas Ale

Our Dry Hopped American Pale Ale (APA) is charged with American hops to create a bold, aromatic ale. Assertive hop flavor joins the pine/citrus aroma characteristic of American hops to balance the full body provided by North American malts. After fermentation, the beer circulates through a bed of whole-cone Cascade and Chinook hops, boosting the distinctive hop aroma of this satisfying ale.

Sunny cousin to the Half Cycle IPA. A single IPA, hopped like a double, with over-the-top hop character. Notes of spice and pine, with citrus coming forward from the zest of blood oranges. Dry hopped with a pound of high alpha American hops in every barrel.

The ?Back Forty? is property commonly found on the outskirts of the Wisconsin family farm. Here uncultivated acres wait prime for adventure- forts, tree houses, rope swings and first kisses! A place to run away, to camp, to climb, to build, to play. Not actually home but not too far away. That?s the Back Forty. The beer you hold is similar both dark and adventurous still smooth and familiar. Here?s a beer you can enjoy without pretense or explanation. Every mind requires some acres of possibility, space for dreams, the great escape, everyone needs a Back Forty.

The CHOUFFE BOK 6666 is a seasonal beer especially brewed for the Netherlands. Bok beers traditionally appear on the Dutch market at the end of September.  The CHOUFFE BOK 6666 stands out from others due to a copper colour, a fresh and fruity scent and a pleasant full-bodied feeling in the mouth, which ends in an aftertaste with a hint of bitterness.
